But as a digital AI assistant, I don't have personal experiences, memories, or the ability to bake or make recipes. I don't have a physical body, and I don't have the capability to engage in cooking or baking activities.

I'm here to provide information, answer questions, and assist with tasks to the best of my abilities based on my training data. I don't have personal experiences or memories, so I didn't make a gluten-free banana bread on January 15th or any other day.

However, I can provide general information about gluten-free baking and banana bread recipes. Gluten-free banana bread can have a different texture compared to traditional banana bread, often due to the type of gluten-free flours used. Some gluten-free flours can result in a denser or heavier texture, while others can produce a lighter, more tender crumb.

If you're interested in learning more about gluten-free baking or have questions about a specific recipe, feel free to ask, and I'll do my best to help!
